thread.title_full: Star Wars' Cantina Band is Australia's top sex song | Daily Mail Online

author: Hannah Moore For Daily Mail Australia
title: Star Wars' Cantina Band is Australia's top sex song
text:
With millions of Australians tuning in every day, Spotify has fast become a crucial part of our lives.
And with just as many people putting together playlists, the music moguls have been able to uncover some damning information about the way Aussies like to have sex.
By combing through playlists designed by users planning to get it on, Spotify were able to definitively declare the number one song Australians are having sex to... and it's not what you'd expect.
In tune: A study of Australian Spotify playlists gave some shocking insights into what's playing in bedrooms around the country
Rather than the dulcet tones of Marvin Gaye or even the sensual beats of The Weeknd, down under it appears Australians prefer swing songs, performed on woodwind.
In a shock victory, the Cantina Band which appears in Star Wars: A New Hope took out the top spot.
The upbeat tune, reminiscent of 1930's big bands, beat out classics like Jermih's Birthday Sex and Ginuwine's Pony.
Sexy? The Star Wars Cantina Band tune from A New Hope topped the list, shocking even the researchers. The song was performed by Bith, recreated here for Monsterpalooza
Understandable: When it came to playlists centred around love, Marvin Gaye's (pictured) Let's Get It On topped the list
AUSTRALIA'S TOP TEN SEX SONGS Cantina Band (from the 'Star Wars: A New Hope' Soundtrack) – John Williams
Birthday Sex – Jeremih
Sex (Cheat Codes X Kris Kross Amsterdam) – Cheat Codes
Sex With Me – Bonus Track – Rihanna
Pony – Ginuwine
Sex on Fire – Kings of Leon
Often – The Weeknd
Earned It – The Weeknd
Thinkin Bout You – Frank Ocean
Slow Motion – Trey Songz
Spotify confirmed the statistic to Daily Mail Australia, noting even they were surprised with the bizarre first place - but it was triple checked.
When it came to more romantic moments, such as Valentine's Day, the songs Australians used in their playlists were a little more conventional.
Ed Sheerhan's Thinking Out Loud topped the list, with crooners John Legend, Sam Smith and Elvis Presley taking four of the five top places.
The same went for Love songs.
Playlists using the word love in their title returned a mixture of songs new and old - with Marvin Gaye's Let's Get It On taking out the top spot.
He was followed by Drake singing Fake Love, international acts James Arthur, Justin Beiber and Ed Sheerhan all got a nod in the top five.
